# Evolution of Applications

## Flow
Standalone → Client-Server → Web(JSP Servlet) → Java EE → Spring → Microservices

## Why Evolution Happened
Each step solves previous limitations

## Breakdown

### [[Standalone_Applications]]
- Single user
- No network

### [[Client_Server]]
- Introduced networking

### [[Servlet_JSP]]
- Browser-based apps

### [[Java_EE]]
- Enterprise standardization

### [[Spring]]
- Simplified Java EE

### [[Microservices]]
- Scalability & independence